4/9/2023, updated on 24/3/2024, 30/10/20: Election Commission of Malaysia (SPR), Tindak Malaysia (2023), Attorney General Chambers, Data.gov.my (archived files), Undi.info. Refer to individual State Candidate Age Source File

There may be discrepancies for the age of candidates as there is no official data released for the attribute. There were clashes between PKR, PSM and PAS at the DUN Level elections There are different interpretations of total valid votes for different parties based on different sources. According to EC Statistics published by MStar website (21/4/2013), there are 112 women candidates. This value excludes one UMNO and one DAP women candidate contesting in Sabah.
